During the course the students acquaint themselves with the requirements for the content, language and form of master's theses. In the seminar they analyse master's theses written earlier and discuss the problems of the theses they plan to write.Objectives/eesmärkid:  The goal of the MA Seminar is to develop independent research skills as well as skills of oral and written presentation, and academic discussion.Learning outcomes/õpiväljund:  The student who has successfully completed the course
- can define a research problem and choose the research topic
- can write research papers
- can present research results 
- can provide constructive feedback on the work of others
